1. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics): The Lovasz Local Lemma is a well-known tool in discrete mathematics, and this paper presents an extension of the lemma and its applications to integer programming, which is a topic in discrete mathematics. 
2. cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper discusses NP-hard integer programs and approximation algorithms, which are topics in computational complexity. 
3. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory): The paper discusses minimax integer programs, which are related to game theory. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper discusses randomized rounding, which is a technique used in machine learning. 
5. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper discusses linear relaxations and constructive (algorithmic) versions of the results, which are topics in numerical analysis.
